title: Attacks in Iraq resulting in 10+ Fatalities, Iraq, 2004-March 2007
name: Attacks in Iraq resulting in 10+ Fatalities, Iraq, 2004-March 2007
description: This data reports terror incidents recorded for Iraq in the National Counter Terrorism Center's World Wide Incident Tracking Database. It covers incidents that were observed for the period 2004 up through March 2007. The Center cautions that there could be some incidents that have occurred in Iraq that is not in the data. There are over 12,000 attacks for Iraq and the victims are of a variety of nationalities, American included. Fatalities, wounded and hostages taken for each record are included in the data.
